Technical reports

W3C publishes a range of technical reports (Standards and supporting Notes) which help move the web forward. Join us and shape future reports.

Such as API, Internationalization, or WAI-ARIA
Advanced search (Draft Standards, Candidate Standards, Standards, Draft Notes, Notes — Accessibility)

Search by reports

Standards
Standards are normative. They are widely reviewed and legal requirements. Sometimes we call them Recommendations. Learn about our Standards process.
Supporting Notes
Notes are informative. They give you use cases, practices, and code examples.
